  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a case control study of the association between burning mouth syndrome and sleep
      dysfunction. Cases will comprise of patients diagnosed with burning mouth syndrome at the
      UCSF oral medicine clinic. Controls will include patients with leukoplakia, pigmented
      lesions, traumatic lesions, benign tumors, mucoceles, and pemphigoid matched on age (5 years)
      and gender to the cases. New patients as well as those presenting for follow-up visits will
      be eligible.

      Each case and control subject will be administered the following 4 questionnaires by
      interview: (1) enrollment questionnaire (2) Sleep scale from the medical outcomes study
      (MOS), (3) current sleep status scale and (4) a numerical rating scale for measurement of
      oral symptoms.

      Cases (BMS patients) will be followed in the clinic or by telephone contact once per month
      for the following 6 months and questionnaires 1 (question 6 only), 2, 3 and 4 will be
      administered by interview.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
